JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 1299
EP  - 1332
VL  - 93
IS  - 4
KW  - Consumer search
KW  - Bayesian learning
KW  - spatial learning
KW  - online platforms
KW  - recommendation systems
KW  - path dependence
KW  - Gaussian processes
KW  - approximate dynamic programming
KW  - neural networks
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA19576
Y2  - 2026/04/24
N2  - We develop and estimate a model of consumer search with spatial learning. Consumers make inferences from previously searched objects to unsearched objects that are nearby in attribute space, generating path dependence in search sequences. The estimated model rationalizes patterns in data on online consumer search paths: search tends to converge to the chosen product in attribute space, and consumers take larger steps away from rarely purchased products. Eliminating spatial learning reduces consumer welfare by 12%: cross-product inferences allow consumers to locate better products in a shorter time. Spatial learning has important implications for product recommendations on retail platforms. We show that consumer welfare can be reduced by unrepresentative product recommendations and that consumer-optimal product recommendations depend on both consumer learning and competition between platforms.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Selecting the Most Effective Nudge: Evidence From a Large-Scale Experiment on Immunization
AU  - Banerjee, Abhijit
AU  - Chandrasekhar, Arun G.
AU  - Dalpath, Suresh
AU  - Duflo, Esther
AU  - Floretta, John
AU  - Jackson, Matthew O.
AU  - Kannan, Harini
AU  - Loza, Francine
AU  - Sankar, Anirudh
AU  - Schrimpf, Anna
AU  - Shrestha, Maheshwor
Y1  - 2025/07/01
